My name is Richard Anderson, and I am in my last year as a Mathematics and Physics Undergraduate at The University of Texas at El Paso. I have 3 cumullative years of research experience, having worked on projects in theoretical astrophysics, compuational particle physics, applications of machine learning to computer vision, and effective field theory simulations.

